   <body>
      <section>
         <indexterm>life cycle monitoring</indexterm>
      </section>
      <section>
         <p>The standard Life Cycle Monitoring (LCM) feature uses
basic time counters for the monitored components. For each component
an initial expected lifetime is configured at first start-up of the
product, and this lifetime will be decreased by the same value day
by day until it reaches zero.</p>
         <p>The actual operating conditions
of the component will have no impact on the estimated remaining lifetime,
only the time in operation has. This means that the estimated lifetime
will not be accurate, except if the component is only exposed to the
wear and exact conditions taken into account when the initial nominal
lifetime was calculated.</p>
      </section>
      <section>
         <title>Life Cycle Reminders</title>
         <p>There are five possible
reminders.<table>
               <tgroup cols="2">
                  <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="20%"/>
                  <colspec colname="col2"/>
                  <thead>
                     <row>
                        <entry valign="top">#</entry>
                        <entry valign="top">Reminder</entry>
                     </row>
                  </thead>
                  <tbody>
                     <row>
                        <entry>1</entry>
                        <entry>Start-up
reminder</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry>2</entry>
                        <entry>Fan module replacement recommended</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry>3</entry>
                        <entry>Battery replacement recommended</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry>4</entry>
                        <entry>Power module replacement recommended</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry>5</entry>
                        <entry>Air filter replacement recommended</entry>
                     </row>
                     <row>
                        <entry>6</entry>
                        <entry>Warranty expired</entry>
                     </row>
                  </tbody>
               </tgroup>
            </table>After a configured period (individual periods for each reminder),
an event pop-up is shown on the display and the event is logged in
the event log. </p>
      </section>
